This is my friend Guo Jing's diary.

It records the real life experience and psychological feeling of the women who lived alone in Wuhan during the period of Fengcheng.

These words bear witness to Guo's journey from adapting to a sudden crisis to rebuilding her daily life to trying to help others.

12 March
For the past week or two, I woke up first thing every morning to look at the latest disease map. At first, the number of confirmed cases in Wuhan was still around 30,000. I silently calculated when it would drop to 20,000 based on the number of new cases being treated each day, at 20,000, it seemed like a small goal in my mind to figure out when it would come down to 10,000. I don't know what it means. It seems like hope.
21 pieces of meat

Yesterday afternoon more than 6:00, the director of the property notice everyone lead to buy 10 yuan a catty of meat, each 4 catties. I went downstairs to get some meat. This time the meat is frozen, so it's easier to cut. I divided the meat into 21 portions. That's almost enough for a month.

Shortly after 9 p.m. , someone sent a letter of apology from the Gangdu Garden Management Committee, saying: On the afternoon of March 11,2020, due to a work error, we delivered 1,000 meals in a sanitation truck during the delivery of centrally purchased inexpensive meat for residents, of these, 530 have been distributed without strictly implementing the relevant requirements for clean transportation of food, which has adversely affected the physical and mental health of the population. For this we sincerely apologize to the residents.

"How did the meat come from our neighborhood? " Asked one resident. Someone posted a photo of a bus full of meat.

Retweets from the neighborhood

The property director replied: "The meat of our community is the community car to the supermarket directly towed to the community. "

I remembered that the people in the back of the train in snowland were eating chunks of protein made from cockroaches. It's hard for us who are stuck inside to know what's going on outside, to be sure what's going on with the food we're getting.

Meat on the floor of a property office
Last night's dinner was stir-fried pork with celery and porridge.

It was cloudy in the morning, so I didn't go downstairs. It rained in the afternoon, and the Sun came out in the afternoon. The afternoon in the community is not the sun, I have no incentive to go downstairs.

Some people in the community group sent out "Wuhan Public Notice of the latest list of no epidemic community" and asked "why we have not our community AH? "

"there are only two buildings in the other community that are not affected by the outbreak. "

"As long as we don't have patients in our neighborhood, we don't have to worry about being on the list. "

"The lifting of the ban in Wuhan must be based on the fact that there is no epidemic in this reported community. If there is a quarantined person in our community, we will never be on the list. "

"For the sake of the reputation of the community, ask our grid worker. "

Someone started calling, saying, "the community has been unable to get through to the Party secretary, and is not answering his phone. The grid worker is not answering his phone, either, to see if anyone has any other contact information. "

Someone called the community, said: "The community response, our community has been reported, is waiting for approval and announcement. "

The reason for all this anxiety is the hope of an early unsealing.

When I was cooking lunch, I took a carrot and found it was broken. After I bought the potatoes and the carrots, I put them in the cupboard and didn't really look at them. I quickly took them out and examined them. Some potatoes and carrots sprouted.

I looked it up and found that carrots can be eaten after sprouting, but the nutrition and taste are not fresh good. However, sprouted potatoes produce Solanine, a neurotoxin that can cause vomiting, diarrhea and, in severe cases, death. Cooking at high temperatures has only a limited destructive effect on Solanine.

These potatoes and carrots were bought on February 26, the last time I was out of the neighborhood. I am very sorry for the waste of vegetables, regret that I saved too much, regret that I did not store vegetables timely inspection.

In the afternoon, community workers knock on the door and ask for names, phone numbers and identification numbers. I asked through the door: "Why are you collecting this information? " The man outside replied: "The community is confirming the information. " It seems that he is just a man to carry out orders. I couldn't argue with him, I couldn't refuse him, so I gave him the information.

An hour later, a member of the community called me to confirm the information, i asked again, "why do you need to register your ID number? " The community worker said, "if you want to enter it into the system, you can find out later if there are any problems in the system, such as whether each house is occupied, whether it is owned by the owner or the tenant, how many people there are, what is the relationship. That's what it says."

"When will it be unsealed? "

"The current notice is that we can not resume work until 20 days ago. Now the growth is in single digits, and the later growth is zero. According to the specific circumstances, the seal has not been lifted yet, so we must strictly control in and out. "

What are the necessary social controls? We are now sealed in the community, where can not go, statistics of the residents of the information for the control of the disease and what role. I'm afraid this is a chance for the "higher ups" to tighten up their oversight. I was filled with apprehension when I saw the real-name registration measure yesterday. Delivering more privacy is another price we have to pay in this epidemic.

March 13th

Before the closure of the city, occasionally to camping or to the countryside to play, quiet in the flowers will make people happy. Now I wake up every day to the sound of birds, but I am not in a relaxed and happy mood.

I think of these years occasionally heard a city people want to be a farmer, I would like to listen. Most of these people feel that the city is competitive, the pressure of work, the pace of life is fast, and grasp what, they want to farm the countryside, to live a self-sufficient life. These people's ideas ignore the hardships of the farmers, a bit arrogant and self-centered.

I was a farmer when I was a kid, and those days were tough. Our family has more than 20 mu of land, all by hand sowing and harvesting, weeding and scattering fertilizer. I've been working in the fields since I was seven or eight. It was summer in June, and the weather was hot, and it was the time of the harvest. In order to cool down, we are early out of the night, we went to the field at dawn to harvest wheat, back home are dark, in the field at noon to eat dry instant noodles, thirsty to drink chrysanthemum crystal bubble water.

Wheat Harvest to bend, after a few days will be back pain, severe pain on his knees to cut. In the hot sun a day will also be dizzy, can not only endure, wheat cutting can not rest.

After the wheat is cut, the threshing machine is put into operation. Some people have to stuff the wheat ears into the machine. After the wheat grains and stalks are separated, they come out from different mouths. Some people have to dig the wheat grains to prevent accumulation. The wheat grain occasionally flies out from the Straw's mouth, hits on the body lets the human ache to shed tears. I've been thinking about getting it over with since I started.

Being a farmer so hard, but also depends on the weather to eat, whether it is a drought or flood will affect the harvest. Honestly, I don't want to be a farmer anymore. Farmers Farm for a living, not for the pleasure of idling.

14 March

A friend pulled me into a group where people shared the latest traffic-control information and "leave" experiences. Some counties and cities in Hubei, except Wuhan, have begun to relax some controls. Some are eager to leave, some are eager to return to work, some are eager to reunite, and some just want to leave. Of course, some people want to go back to Hubei, but many train tickets do not sell tickets to the Hubei region.

To leave, one must have a pass and a health certificate. However, each county, city or village has different levels of openness and policies. Some passes can only be used in cities, and some places have inter-city buses, some places can drive themselves out of the province by high speed.

Out of Hubei, can enter other provinces and cities is also a problem, access also requires the work unit or community open acceptance certificate. Some provinces do not recognize the Green Code (health code) applied for on Alipay, some people drive on the highway, to the destination but can not get off the highway, to Jiangxi, Sichuan, Chongqing Group of friends have encountered such a situation, they were forced to return the same way.

There are places that are open to entry, but they require a 14-day quarantine. Wenzhou, Taizhou and Guangzhou are demanding concentrated isolation at their own expense, at 300 yuan per person per day, while Dongguan and Hangzhou are demanding concentrated isolation for 14 days at the government's expense.

Without a unified and stable policy, people's travel is difficult to guarantee, often only their own personal experiment, the experiment will pay some unnecessary costs.

16 March
A few days ago, a netizen exposed the medical staff during the outbreak of wages but less than usual. That's because health care workers are paid a performance bonus in addition to their minimum wage, and some are paid less during outbreaks when hospitals only hand out subsidies to minimum wage.

Of course, there is a problem with the health care system. Our public hospitals are also self-financing. The salaries of health care workers depend on performance. We are often required to do excessive examinations when we see doctors, to be marketed as expensive drugs. It can also lead to doctor-patient conflict.

Yesterday, the South Wind Window article revealed the construction of the Vulcan Mountain, the plight of the workers, a worker went to the Vulcan Mountain Handyman was told two nights 800 yuan, a leader came to ask only to find two nights is 3,000 yuan. Eight of them workers to the project department, and finally, the shift leader took 200 yuan, the workers get 2,800.

The workers are to be quarantined for 15 days and receive a daily quarantine allowance of 300 yuan. Workers who claim benefits need to provide proof of segregation. They go to the community, and the community asks them to prove that they are part of the community. There are a lot of workers who haven't been paid for segregation.

Health Care Workers, construction workers, they are in the outbreak of the virus at risk, with fear to continue to work. But now, before the epidemic was over, they were treated unfairly. We can't just glorify sacrifice and keep our voices down.

18 March

Someone said: "The situation in Wuhan is getting better" , Wuhan's epidemic is indeed getting better, but the epidemic caused isolation, panic, sacrifice, trauma is getting better? New coronary pneumonia will give some patients with physical sequelae, but also caused in Wuhan people's psychological sequelae, which takes how long to get better?

Dr. Brooklyn, the founder of the Brooklyn Trauma Center, said of trauma that people who lived through 9 / 11 suffered relatively little trauma. He mentions three important influences: action, attention, and storytelling.

"action" means that people can act when a disaster occurs, such as the World Trade Center bombing, people can move their bodies, can run away from the disaster site. Action Represents Power and control. "attention" means that 911 received worldwide attention and support, and that the United States government established the 911 Victims Compensation Fund, which was extended until Oct. 1,2090. "telling" is the ability for people to talk about their experiences without being accused of telling them.

By contrast, in this outbreak, from Fengcheng to Fengqu, our space for action is gradually shrinking, we are trapped. In terms of attention, Wuhan did get the world's attention, but support was once blocked, doctors were not allowed to seek help from society without permission from hospitals, and volunteer medical supplies were intercepted by official agencies. A lot of the attention is hard to translate into practical help. As for narratives, some narratives are being blocked, and many netizens have prepared backup numbers for microblogs.

The 911 memorial bears the names of the victims

In fact, we still have a lot of things to do, to record the deaths of the epidemic, spread the true information of the epidemic, accountability and so on. A lot of people are doing it, but people's movements are limited, there are things that individuals want to do but can't do, have no power. People are encouraged to act productively, motivated to continue, and easily discouraged if they are frequently frustrated.

When tragedy strikes, the truth is dismissed as rumor, and "positive energy" is trumpeted. When social attention to tragedy is limited and accountability is not reciprocated, people's emotions are slowly consumed, anger dissipates, and powerlessness increases.

Sometimes, when I see people writing about a social event, I don't have the energy to go in and read the details. Because when I know something's wrong, I want to be able to do something, not just be a spectator. But individuals have limited social resources and power, and we don't make the decisions that change things. To protect ourselves, we occasionally need to turn off some of our emotions and distance ourselves from reality.

Emotions are one of the ways we perceive the world. When we turn off our emotions, we stop thinking, we stop knowing and understanding the world. People Begin to passively accept information, it is difficult to distinguish between rumors and facts, in order to change, rumors flying in the circumstances more prone to panic and anxiety.

12 March

For the past week or two, I woke up first thing every morning to look at the latest disease map. At first, the number of confirmed cases in Wuhan was still around 30,000. I silently calculated when it would drop to 20,000 based on the number of new cases being treated each day, at 20,000, it seemed like a small goal in my mind to figure out when it would come down to 10,000. I don't know what it means. It seems like hope.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
21 pieces of meat

Yesterday afternoon more than 6:00, the director of the property notice everyone lead to buy 10 yuan a catty of meat, each 4 catties. I went downstairs to get some meat. This time the meat is frozen, so it's easier to cut. I divided the meat into 21 portions. That's almost enough for a month.

Shortly after 9 p.m. , someone sent a letter of apology from the Gangdu Garden Management Committee, saying: On the afternoon of March 11,2020, due to a work error, we delivered 1,000 meals in a sanitation truck during the delivery of centrally purchased inexpensive meat for residents, of these, 530 have been distributed without strictly implementing the relevant requirements for clean transportation of food, which has adversely affected the physical and mental health of the population. For this we sincerely apologize to the residents.

"How did the meat come from our neighborhood? " Asked one resident. Someone posted a photo of a bus full of meat.

Some people in the community group sent out "Wuhan Public Notice of the latest list of no epidemic community" and asked "why we have not our community AH? "

"there are only two buildings in the other community that are not affected by the outbreak. "

"As long as we don't have patients in our neighborhood, we don't have to worry about being on the list. "

"The lifting of the ban in Wuhan must be based on the fact that there is no epidemic in this reported community. If there is a quarantined person in our community, we will never be on the list. "

"For the sake of the reputation of the community, ask our grid worker. "

Someone started calling, saying, "the community has been unable to get through to the Party secretary, and is not answering his phone. The grid worker is not answering his phone, either, to see if anyone has any other contact information. "

The reason for all this anxiety is the hope of an early unsealing.

When I was cooking lunch, I took a carrot and found it was broken. After I bought the potatoes and the carrots, I put them in the cupboard and didn't really look at them. I quickly took them out and examined them. Some potatoes and carrots sprouted.

I looked it up and found that carrots can be eaten after sprouting, but the nutrition and taste are not fresh good. However, sprouted potatoes produce Solanine, a neurotoxin that can cause vomiting, diarrhea and, in severe cases, death. Cooking at high temperatures has only a limited destructive effect on Solanine.

These potatoes and carrots were bought on February 26, the last time I was out of the neighborhood. I am very sorry for the waste of vegetables, regret that I saved too much, regret that I did not store vegetables timely inspection.

In the afternoon, community workers knock on the door and ask for names, phone numbers and identification numbers. I asked through the door: "Why are you collecting this information? " The man outside replied: "The community is confirming the information. " It seems that he is just a man to carry out orders. I couldn't argue with him, I couldn't refuse him, so I gave him the information.

An hour later, a member of the community called me to confirm the information, i asked again, "why do you need to register your ID number? " The community worker said, "if you want to enter it into the system, you can find out later if there are any problems in the system, such as whether each house is occupied, whether it is owned by the owner or the tenant, how many people there are, what is the relationship. That's what it says."

"When will it be unsealed? "

"The current notice is that we can not resume work until 20 days ago. Now the growth is in single digits, and the later growth is zero. According to the specific circumstances, the seal has not been lifted yet, so we must strictly control in and out. "

What are the necessary social controls? We are now sealed in the community, where can not go, statistics of the residents of the information for the control of the disease and what role. I'm afraid this is a chance for the "higher ups" to tighten up their oversight. I was filled with apprehension when I saw the real-name registration measure yesterday. Delivering more privacy is another price we have to pay in this epidemic.

March 13th

Before the closure of the city, occasionally to camping or to the countryside to play, quiet in the flowers will make people happy. Now I wake up every day to the sound of birds, but I am not in a relaxed and happy mood.

I think of these years occasionally heard a city people want to be a farmer, I would like to listen. Most of these people feel that the city is competitive, the pressure of work, the pace of life is fast, and grasp what, they want to farm the countryside, to live a self-sufficient life. These people's ideas ignore the hardships of the farmers, a bit arrogant and self-centered.

I was a farmer when I was a kid, and those days were tough. Our family has more than 20 mu of land, all by hand sowing and harvesting, weeding and scattering fertilizer. I've been working in the fields since I was seven or eight. It was summer in June, and the weather was hot, and it was the time of the harvest. In order to cool down, we are early out of the night, we went to the field at dawn to harvest wheat, back home are dark, in the field at noon to eat dry instant noodles, thirsty to drink chrysanthemum crystal bubble water.

Wheat Harvest to bend, after a few days will be back pain, severe pain on his knees to cut. In the hot sun a day will also be dizzy, can not only endure, wheat cutting can not rest.

After the wheat is cut, the threshing machine is put into operation. Some people have to stuff the wheat ears into the machine. After the wheat grains and stalks are separated, they come out from different mouths. Some people have to dig the wheat grains to prevent accumulation. The wheat grain occasionally flies out from the Straw's mouth, hits on the body lets the human ache to shed tears. I've been thinking about getting it over with since I started.

Being a farmer so hard, but also depends on the weather to eat, whether it is a drought or flood will affect the harvest. Honestly, I don't want to be a farmer anymore. Farmers Farm for a living, not for the pleasure of idling.

14 March

A friend pulled me into a group where people shared the latest traffic-control information and "leave" experiences. Some counties and cities in Hubei, except Wuhan, have begun to relax some controls. Some are eager to leave, some are eager to return to work, some are eager to reunite, and some just want to leave. Of course, some people want to go back to Hubei, but many train tickets do not sell tickets to the Hubei region.

To leave, one must have a pass and a health certificate. However, each county, city or village has different levels of openness and policies. Some passes can only be used in cities, and some places have inter-city buses, some places can drive themselves out of the province by high speed.

Out of Hubei, can enter other provinces and cities is also a problem, access also requires the work unit or community open acceptance certificate. Some provinces do not recognize the Green Code (health code) applied for on Alipay, some people drive on the highway, to the destination but can not get off the highway, to Jiangxi, Sichuan, Chongqing Group of friends have encountered such a situation, they were forced to return the same way.

There are places that are open to entry, but they require a 14-day quarantine. Wenzhou, Taizhou and Guangzhou are demanding concentrated isolation at their own expense, at 300 yuan per person per day, while Dongguan and Hangzhou are demanding concentrated isolation for 14 days at the government's expense.

Without a unified and stable policy, people's travel is difficult to guarantee, often only their own personal experiment, the experiment will pay some unnecessary costs.

15 March

Another tragedy has occurred in Hubei. Yesterday, a netizen posted a message on Weibo that a woman with mental problems went downstairs to take food from people in Xiaogan's Lisi district. The neighbor sent her home, only to find that her house smelled bad. Her one-and-a-half-year-old child had starved to death for more than ten days.

The Information Office of the Xiaogan Municipal People's government released a message on its official microblog, "Xiaogan release, " which said that it was discovered and reported by community cadres when they went home to investigate. After investigation, women home rice, milk powder, vegetables, fruits and other living materials.

When I saw the news, I was filled with panic and sorrow. Kids cry when they're hungry, too, right? Little ones learn to take it in silence. "Xiaogan posted" on two related microblogs, both of which have declined to comment. If the posts are true, why be afraid to comment? Dr. Li Wen Liang has more than 610,000 comments on his Weibo Account.

A few days ago, a netizen exposed the medical staff during the outbreak of wages but less than usual. That's because health care workers are paid a performance bonus in addition to their minimum wage, and some are paid less during outbreaks when hospitals only hand out subsidies to minimum wage.

Of course, there is a problem with the health care system. Our public hospitals are also self-financing. The salaries of health care workers depend on performance. 17 March

Some places in Hubei have also been unsealed for a few days, but the phenomenon of changing day and night is confusing. Yesterday a friend of Macheng's in the group said, "Macheng will close the city again tomorrow. " Someone asked, "why? " The man didn't know. He said the village had just sent a notice, "There has been a change in policy, " he said. "The expressway will be closed tomorrow morning at 9 am. Those who have applied for a pass should return to their posts as soon as possible. ". Everyone's getting nervous. Get those who have passes out of here.

A group of friends drove to the pass said: "Today got the pass, the police station told me to leave, or a day a policy, then do not blame him. "

After a friend's community in Hubei was unsealed for a few days, suddenly one day, her family received a message from somewhere, saying it was a secret message not to be told. It was said that their city was to close the city again, she and her family rushed to stock up on food like rice and oil, only to be told a few hours later that it was a rumor that the city would be closed again.

Changing the government day in and day out will make the government lose credibility and make people feel insecure and at a loss.

18 March

Someone said: "The situation in Wuhan is getting better" , Wuhan's epidemic is indeed getting better, but the epidemic caused isolation, panic, sacrifice, trauma is getting better? New coronary pneumonia will give some patients with physical sequelae, but also caused in Wuhan people's psychological sequelae, which takes how long to get better?

Dr. Brooklyn, the founder of the Brooklyn Trauma Center, said of trauma that people who lived through 9 / 11 suffered relatively little trauma. He mentions three important influences: action, attention, and storytelling.

"action" means that people can act when a disaster occurs, such as the World Trade Center bombing, people can move their bodies, can run away from the disaster site. Action Represents Power and control. "attention" means that 911 received worldwide attention and support, and that the United States government established the 911 Victims Compensation Fund, which was extended until Oct. 1,2090. "telling" is the ability for people to talk about their experiences without being accused of telling them.

By contrast, in this outbreak, from Fengcheng to Fengqu, our space for action is gradually shrinking, we are trapped. In terms of attention, Wuhan did get the world's attention, but support was once blocked, doctors were not allowed to seek help from society without permission from hospitals, and volunteer medical supplies were intercepted by official agencies. A lot of the attention is hard to translate into practical help. As for narratives, some narratives are being blocked, and many netizens have prepared backup numbers for microblogs.

In fact, we still have a lot of things to do, to record the deaths of the epidemic, spread the true information of the epidemic, accountability and so on. A lot of people are doing it, but people's movements are limited, there are things that individuals want to do but can't do, have no power. People are encouraged to act productively, motivated to continue, and easily discouraged if they are frequently frustrated.

When tragedy strikes, the truth is dismissed as rumor, and "positive energy" is trumpeted. When social attention to tragedy is limited and accountability is not reciprocated, people's emotions are slowly consumed, anger dissipates, and powerlessness increases.

Sometimes, when I see people writing about a social event, I don't have the energy to go in and read the details. Because when I know something's wrong, I want to be able to do something, not just be a spectator. But individuals have limited social resources and power, and we don't make the decisions that change things. To protect ourselves, we occasionally need to turn off some of our emotions and distance ourselves from reality.

Emotions are one of the ways we perceive the world. When we turn off our emotions, we stop thinking, we stop knowing and understanding the world. People Begin to passively accept information, it is difficult to distinguish between rumors and facts, in order to change, rumors flying in the circumstances more prone to panic and anxiety.

Said it was a tip, because I don't have the official notice, and I don't know if it's true or not. I don't really care anymore, in case it doesn't work out. The same seems to be true of other residents, and no one has responded.

See"somebody goes out","somebody is infected", persuade everybody not to go out of the news, everybody reply is positive however.

In the afternoon, a resident posted a message in the cluster: from March 13 to March 17, there were daily new cases from outpatient clinics, and today's one was a manager of a vegetable market in the Kong Hon district. It means there's still a source of infection out there, so don't let down your guard and don't go out. If you have to go out, you have to protect yourself. At the same time, it's best to keep a distance of more than 2.5 meters between people, and reduce the number of group purchases accordingly, just enough to get by. Instant likes and endorsements.

Spirit of the town hall meeting:

Those stranded on the 22nd may return to the Han Dynasty Point to point. Stranded in Hubei, Chinese can leave Hubei point-to-point

On the 26th, the doors were unsealed and residents were allowed to move around the community.

On the 29th, the community was unsealed and residents returned to work on foot with health codes, work certificates and private cars.

On the 31st, the production and market operation of enterprises gradually resumed normal operation.

Normalization of key business premises on 2 April.
